Load libraries

library(tidyverse) # data manipulation
library(ggpubr) # producing data exploratory plots
library(modelsummary) # descriptive data 
library(glmmTMB) # running generalised mixed models 
library(DHARMa) # model diagnostics 
library(performance) # model diagnostics  
library(ggeffects) # partial effect plots 
library(car) # running Anova on model 
library(emmeans) # post-hoc analysis  
library(MuMIn) 
library(patchwork)
m3 <- read_csv("import_data/2-5_month_size_data_2022_2023.csv") |> 
  mutate(across(1:15,factor)) |> 
  mutate(STANDARD_LENGTH =LENGTH, 
         .keep = "unused") |> 
  select(!(NOTES)) |> 
  select(1:15,"STANDARD_LENGTH","MASS")|> 
  group_by(CLUTCH_NUMBER) |> 
  mutate(DENSITY = n()) |> 
  ungroup()
## Rows: 1372 Columns: 19
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr  (8): DATE_OF_HATCH, DATE_SAMPLED, MALE, FEMALE, REGION, POPULATION, AGE...
## dbl (11): CLUTCH_NUMBER, TEMPERATURE, TANK, LEVEL, REPLICATE, CLUTCH_ORDER, ...
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
adult <- read_csv("import_data/adult_size_2022_2023.csv") |> 
  mutate(across(1:3,factor), 
         MALE = FISH_ID, 
         FEMALE = FISH_ID, 
         POPULATION = str_sub(FISH_ID, 2,4), 
         POPULATION = case_when(POPULATION == "ARL" ~ "Arlington Reef", 
                                POPULATION == "SUD" ~ "Sudbury Reef",
                                POPULATION == "VLA" ~ "Vlassof cay",
                                POPULATION == "PRE" ~ "Pretty patches", 
                                TRUE ~ POPULATION)) |> 
  left_join(select(m3, c("MALE","TEMPERATURE")), 
             by="MALE") |> 
  left_join(select(m3, c("FEMALE","TEMPERATURE")), 
             by="FEMALE") |>
  distinct() |> 
  mutate(TEMPERATURE = coalesce(TEMPERATURE.x, TEMPERATURE.y)) |> 
  drop_na(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  select(-c("TEMPERATURE.x","TEMPERATURE.y"))
## Rows: 101 Columns: 7
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (4): FISH_ID, SEX, fin_clip1, fin_clip2
## dbl (3): TANK, SL, MASS
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
m3_df_all <- m3 |> 
  left_join(select(adult, c("MALE", "SL", "MASS")), 
            by ="MALE") |> 
  mutate(SL_MALE =SL, 
         MASS_MALE =MASS.y, 
         .keep = "unused") |>
  left_join(select(adult, c("FEMALE", "SL", "MASS")), 
            by ="FEMALE") |> 
  mutate(SL_FEMALE =SL, 
         MASS_FEMALE =MASS, 
         .keep ="unused") |> 
  mutate(SL_MIDPOINT = (SL_MALE+SL_FEMALE)/2, 
         MASS_MIDPOINT = (MASS_MALE+MASS_FEMALE)/2, 
         AGE_DAYS =as.numeric(AGE_DAYS)) |> 
  rename(MASS =MASS.x)

Models

Random factors

modelNULL <- glmmTMB(MASS ~ 1, 
                  family=gaussian(),
                  data =m3_df_all)

model1 <- glmmTMB(MASS ~ (1|MALE), 
                  family=gaussian(),
                  data = m3_df_all)

AIC(modelNULL, model1) 
BIC(modelNULL, model1)

Main hypothesis

model1a <- glmmTMB(MASS ~ scale(MASS_MALE, center=TRUE)*TEMPERATURE + scale(DENSITY, center=TRUE) 
                   + scale(AGE_DAYS, center=FALSE) + (1| MALE),                     
                   family=gaussian(), 
                   data=m3_df_all)

Alternative hypothesis

model1b <- glmmTMB(MASS ~ scale(MASS_MALE, center=TRUE)*TEMPERATURE + scale(DENSITY, center=TRUE)  
                   + scale(AGE_DAYS, center=FALSE) + scale(as.numeric(PARENTAL_DAYS_IN_TREATMENT), center=TRUE)  + (1| MALE),
                   family=gaussian(), 
                   data=m3_df_all)

Model selection

AIC(model1a, model1b, k=6)

Summary figure

m3.mass <- emmeans(model1b, ~ MASS_MALE*TEMPERATURE, type="response",
                 at =list(MASS_MALE=seq(from =min(m3_df_all$MASS_MALE), to =max(m3_df_all$MASS_MALE), by=.1)))

m3.mass.df <- as.data.frame(m3.mass)

m3.mass.obs <- drop_na(m3_df_all, MASS_MALE, MASS) |> 
  mutate(Pred =predict(model1b, re.form=NA, type ='response'), 
         Resid =residuals(model1b, type ='response'), 
         Fit =Pred+Resid) 

m3.mass.obs.summarize <-  m3.mass.obs |> 
  group_by(MALE, TEMPERATURE) |> 
  summarise(mean.mass =mean(Fit, na.rm=TRUE), 
            mean.mass.male =mean(MASS_MALE, na.rm = TRUE), 
            sd.mass =sd(Fit, na.rm =TRUE), 
            n.mass = n()) |> 
  mutate(se.mass = sd.mass / sqrt(n.mass), 
         lower.ci.mass =mean.mass - qt(1-(0.05/2), n.mass -1) * se.mass, 
         upper.ci.mass =mean.mass + qt(1-(0.05/2), n.mass -1) * se.mass) |> 
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'MALE'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
m3.mass.obs.summarize2 <- m3.mass.obs.summarize |> 
  group_by(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  mutate(temp_mean =mean(mean.mass), 
         temp_sd =sd(mean.mass)) |> 
  distinct(temp_mean, .keep_all = TRUE) 

mod = lm(mean.mass ~ mean.mass.male*TEMPERATURE,  
         data =m3.mass.obs.summarize)

mod.mass <- emmeans(mod, ~ mean.mass.male*TEMPERATURE, 
                 at =list(mean.mass.male=seq(from =min(m3.mass.obs.summarize$mean.mass.male), to =max(m3.mass.obs.summarize$mean.mass.male), by=.25))) |> as.data.frame()

m3.plot <- ggplot(data = m3.mass.df, aes(x=MASS_MALE, y=response)) + 
  stat_smooth(data=m3.mass.obs.summarize, aes(x =mean.mass.male, 
                                                  y =mean.mass, color=TEMPERATURE), 
              method = "lm", 
              se=FALSE) + 
  geom_ribbon(data=mod.mass, aes(x =mean.mass.male, 
                                                  y =emmean, 
                               ymin=lower.CL, ymax=upper.CL, fill=TEMPERATURE), alpha=0.5) +
  geom_pointrange(data = m3.mass.obs.summarize, aes(x =mean.mass.male, 
                                                  y =mean.mass, 
                                                  ymin =lower.ci.mass, 
                                                  ymax =upper.ci.mass, 
                                                  color = TEMPERATURE)) +  
  scale_color_manual(values = c("#69d7d8","#ff9c56", "#903146")) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values =c("#69d7d8","#ff9c56", "#903146")) +

  ggtitle("Offspring-male relationship: 1-month offspring") +
  theme_classic()+theme(legend.position = 'none') 

m3.plot2 <- ggplot(m3.mass.obs.summarize, aes(x=TEMPERATURE, y=mean.mass, color=TEMPERATURE)) +

Slopes

add.df <- split(m3.mass.obs.summarize, m3.mass.obs.summarize$TEMPERATURE) |> 
  map(~lm(mean.mass ~ mean.mass.male, data=.)) |> 
  map(summary) |> 
  map_dbl("r.squared") |> 
  as.data.frame()

add.df <- add.df |>
  mutate(TEMPERATURE = row.names(add.df)) |>
  rename(r.sqaured =names(add.df)[1]) 

sd_values <- m3_df_all |> drop_na(MASS) |> group_by(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  summarise(sd =sd(MASS), 
            se =sd(MASS)/sqrt(nrow(m3_df_all)), 
            Lower.CI =mean(MASS) - qt(1-(0.05/2), nrow(m3_df_all) -1) *se, 
            Upper.CI =mean(MASS) + qt(1-(0.05/2), nrow(m3_df_all) -1) *se)  

df.results.1 <- m3.mass.obs.summarize |> 
  group_by(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  do({ 
    mod = lm(mean.mass ~ mean.mass.male, data = .) 
    data.frame(group = "1-months", 
               slope = coef(mod)[2], 
               Heritability = coef(mod)[2]*2)
    }) |> 
  as.data.frame() |> 
  mutate(Heritability = case_when(Heritability <=0 ~ 0, 
                                  TRUE ~ Heritability)) |> 
  inner_join(add.df, by="TEMPERATURE") |> 
  inner_join(sd_values, by="TEMPERATURE"); df.results.1

Within parental variation

cv_within <- m3.mass.obs |> 
  group_by(MALE) |> 
  mutate(mean_value =mean(Fit), 
         sd_value =sd(Fit), 
         CV =(sd_value/mean_value) * 100) |>
  ungroup() |> 
  select(-c("STANDARD_LENGTH","MASS","Pred","Fit","Resid")) |> 
  distinct(MALE, .keep_all=TRUE) 

within_var <- aov(CV ~ TEMPERATURE, 
                  data=cv_within) 
summary(within_var) 
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)
## TEMPERATURE  2   36.7   18.34   0.374  0.691
## Residuals   30 1471.9   49.06
cv_within_summ <- cv_within |> 
  group_by(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  mutate(mean_CV =mean(CV), 
         mean_mean =mean(mean_value), 
         mean_sd =mean(sd_value),
         nsample =n()) |>
  mutate(ser_value = sd_value/sqrt(nsample), 
         lower.ci =mean_CV - qt(1-(0.05/2), nsample -1) * ser_value, 
         upper.ci =mean_CV + qt(1-(0.05/2), nsample -1) * ser_value) |>
  ungroup() |> 
  distinct(TEMPERATURE, .keep_all=TRUE) |> 
  select(c("TEMPERATURE","mean_CV","mean_mean","mean_sd")); cv_within_summ

Among parental variation

cv_among <- cv_within |> 
  group_by(TEMPERATURE) |> 
  mutate(mean_among =mean(CV), 
         sd_among =sd(CV), 
         nsamples=n(),
         cv_among =(sd_among/mean_among)*100) |> 
  ungroup() |> 
  distinct(cv_among, .keep_all = T) |> 
  select(c("TEMPERATURE","cv_among","sd_among","mean_among","nsamples")) |> 
  arrange(TEMPERATURE)

##final cv values
cv_among2 <- data.frame(x=c("27v30","28v30","27v28"))
cv_among2$cv_among[1] =log(cv_among$cv_among[1]/cv_among$cv_among[3]) 
cv_among2$cv_among[2] =log(cv_among$cv_among[2]/cv_among$cv_among[3]) 
cv_among2$cv_among[3] =log(cv_among$cv_among[1]/cv_among$cv_among[2])
